events.description: The Roman legions in Germania Superior refuse to swear loyalty to Galba. They rebel and proclaim Vitellius as emperor.
events.html: • 69 – The Roman legions in Germania Superior refuse to swear loyalty to Galba. They rebel and proclaim Vitellius as emperor.[1]

events.description: The Alemanni cross the frozen Rhine in large numbers, invading the Roman Empire.
events.html: • 366 – The Alemanni cross the frozen Rhine in large numbers, invading the Roman Empire.[2]

events.description: Mercurius becomes Pope John II, the first pope to adopt a new name upon elevation to the papacy.
events.html: • 533 – Mercurius becomes Pope John II, the first pope to adopt a new name upon elevation to the papacy.[3]

events.description: Reconquista: The Emirate of Granada, the last Moorish stronghold in Spain, surrenders.
events.html: • 1492 – Reconquista: The Emirate of Granada, the last Moorish stronghold in Spain, surrenders.[4]

events.description: Trunajaya rebellion: Amangkurat II of Mataram and his bodyguards execute the rebel leader Trunajaya.
events.html: • 1680 – Trunajaya rebellion: Amangkurat II of Mataram and his bodyguards execute the rebel leader Trunajaya.[5]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: American forces under the command of General George Washington repulse a British attack led by General Charles Cornwallis at the Battle of the Assunpink Creek near Trenton, New Jersey.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: American forces under the command of General George Washington repulse a British attack led by General Charles Cornwallis at the Battle of the Assunpink Creek near Trenton, New Jersey.[6]

events.description: Georgia becomes the fourth state to ratify the United States Constitution.
events.html: • 1788 – Georgia becomes the fourth state to ratify the United States Constitution.[7]

events.description: Northwest Indian War: The Big Bottom massacre is committed by Lenape and Wyandot warriors in the Ohio Country, North America.
events.html: • 1791 – Northwest Indian War: The Big Bottom massacre is committed by Lenape and Wyandot warriors in the Ohio Country, North America.[8]

events.description: The British Institution of Civil Engineers is founded by a group of six engineers; Thomas Telford would later become its first president.
events.html: • 1818 – The British Institution of Civil Engineers is founded by a group of six engineers; Thomas Telford would later become its first president.[9]

events.description: American Civil War: The three-day Battle of Stones River ends in a Union victory when the Confederate Army of Tennessee under General Braxton Bragg are repulsed for the final time by the Army of the Cumberland under General William S. Rosecrans.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: The three-day Battle of Stones River ends in a Union victory when the Confederate Army of Tennessee under General Braxton Bragg are repulsed for the final time by the Army of the Cumberland under General William S. Rosecrans.[10]

events.description: Uruguayan War: The Siege of Paysandú ends as the Brazilians and Coloradans capture Paysandú, Uruguay.
events.html: • 1865 – Uruguayan War: The Siege of Paysandú ends as the Brazilians and Coloradans capture Paysandú, Uruguay.[11]

events.description: American statesman and diplomat John Hay announces the Open Door Policy to promote trade with China.
events.html: • 1900 – American statesman and diplomat John Hay announces the Open Door Policy to promote trade with China.[12]

events.description: Chicago Canal opens.
events.html: • 1900 – Chicago Canal opens.[13]

events.description: The second Palmer Raid, ordered by the US Department of Justice, results in 6,000 suspected communists and anarchists being arrested and held without trial.
events.html: • 1920 – The second Palmer Raid, ordered by the US Department of Justice, results in 6,000 suspected communists and anarchists being arrested and held without trial.[14]

events.description: World premiere of the science fiction play R.U.R. by the Czech writer Karel Čapek in a theater in Hradec Králové.
events.html: • 1921 – World premiere of the science fiction play R.U.R. by the Czech writer Karel Čapek in a theater in Hradec Králové.[15]

events.description: World War II: The Cardiff Blitz severely damages the cathedral in Cardiff, Wales.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: The Cardiff Blitz severely damages the cathedral in Cardiff, Wales.[16]

events.description: The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) obtains the conviction of 33 members of a German spy ring headed by Fritz Joubert Duquesne in the largest espionage case in United States history; Also known as the Duquesne Spy Ring.
events.html: • 1942 – The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) obtains the conviction of 33 members of a German spy ring headed by Fritz Joubert Duquesne in the largest espionage case in United States history; Also known as the Duquesne Spy Ring.[17]

events.description: World War II: Manila is captured by Japanese forces, enabling them to control the Philippines.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Manila is captured by Japanese forces, enabling them to control the Philippines.[18]

events.description: Luis Muñoz Marín is inaugurated as the first democratically elected Governor of Puerto Rico.
events.html: • 1949 – Luis Muñoz Marín is inaugurated as the first democratically elected Governor of Puerto Rico.[19]

events.description: India establishes its highest civilian awards, the Bharat Ratna and the Padma Vibhushan.
events.html: • 1954 – India establishes its highest civilian awards, the Bharat Ratna and the Padma Vibhushan.[20]

events.description: Following the assassination of the Panamanian president José Antonio Remón Cantera, his deputy, José Ramón Guizado, takes power, but is quickly deposed after his involvement in Cantera's death is discovered.

events.description: Luna 1, the first spacecraft to reach the vicinity of the Moon and to orbit the Sun, is launched by the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1959 – Luna 1, the first spacecraft to reach the vicinity of the Moon and to orbit the Sun, is launched by the Soviet Union.[22]

events.description: Vietnam War: The Viet Cong wins its first major victory, at the Battle of Ap Bac.

events.description: The second Ibrox disaster kills 66 fans at a Rangers-Celtic association football (soccer) match.
events.html: • 1971 – The second Ibrox disaster kills 66 fans at a Rangers-Celtic association football (soccer) match.[25]

events.description: United States President Richard Nixon signs a bill lowering the maximum U.S. speed limit to 55 mph in order to conserve gasoline during an OPEC embargo.

events.description: At the opening of a new railway line, a bomb blast at Samastipur, Bihar, India, fatally wounds Lalit Narayan Mishra, Minister of Railways.

events.description: The Federal Rules of Evidence are approved by the United States Congress.
events.html: • 1975 – The Federal Rules of Evidence are approved by the United States Congress.[28]
